comments: Murray (SAC) lifts and re-plants his pivot foot prior to releasing his dribble.
Allen (PHX) brings his hands forward toward Murray's (SAC) path and marginal contact occurs with Murray's front as he starts his dribble.
Nurkic (PHX) briefly has his left arm around Sabonis' (SAC) left arm before correcting during the rebound.
Sabonis (SAC) brings his right hand toward the ball during the rebound and incidental arm contact occurs with Nurkic (PHX).

Nurkic (PHX) brings his right hand toward the ball and marginal contact occurs with Barnes' (SAC) face after Barnes gathers the rebound. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Beal (PHX) contests the layup attempt and marginal contact occurs with Barnes' (SAC) right arm after the release.
Nurkic (PHX) is slightly extending forward as he establishes himself in Barnes' (SAC) path and he does not deliver illegal contact during the screen.
Murray (SAC) and Sabonis (SAC) each bring a hand toward Nurkic's (PHX) back and marginal contact occurs as Nurkic mistimes his jump during the rebound.
Booker (PHX) cleanly dislodges the ball away from Sabonis (SAC) prior to incidental contact occurring.

Nurkic (PHX) is backing up toward Sabonis (SAC) after the ball becomes loose again and marginal body contact occurs when they come together, which occurs simultaneously with Sabonis tripping over Murray's (SAC) foot.
Allen (PHX) is moving forward slightly as Barnes (SAC) cuts back toward the basket and marginal body contact occurs when they come together at the end of the drive.
Allen's (PHX) left forearm and leg each come forward slightly prior to marginal contact occurring with Barnes' (SAC) right side and lower body during his upward shooting motion.
Barnes (SAC) cleanly dislodges the ball away from Allen (PHX) as simultaneous incidental contact occurs during the rebound.
Allen (PHX) dives to the floor and makes clean contact with the ball as simultaneous incidental contact occurs with Barnes (SAC).
Allen's (PHX) back makes contact out of bounds while he is still in possession of the ball on the sideline.
Beal (PHX) briefly has his left arm around Fox's (SAC) midsection before correcting and cleanly dislodges the ball away from Fox as the pass is made.
Allen (PHX) avoids making contact with Fox's (SAC) left arm and legally contests the driving shot attempt.
Sabonis (SAC) extends his hands into Durant's (PHX) back and initiates contact that affects Durant's body trajectory as he elevates for the rebound.
Allen (PHX) legally contests Fox's (SAC) jump shot attempt.
Barnes (SAC) and Durant (PHX) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Sabonis (SAC) faces Nurkic (PHX) up and wraps his left arm around Nurkic's right side as Nurkic elevates for the rebound.
Beal (PHX) commits a take foul on Fox (SAC). The contact occurs prior to Fox's gather.
Beal (PHX) moves to align alongside Fox's (SAC) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Beal's (PHX) left wrist makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Fox (SAC) prior to incidental contact occurring during Fox's upward shooting motion.
